The current rules related to the value of the space key is very restrictive.   Jira offers a much more powerfull mechanism by allowing to set a regular expression to validate a project key.  Such approach would be beneficial in Conflulence.  

This request is made in the context of an integration between several systems.  Currently, due to this lack of flexibility Confluence's space keys cannot follow the key nomenclature established by another system.  On the other hand Jira does not have this limitation.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
