i have employees that copy excel cells into confluence pages.

the rendered cells as an HTML table look pretty good as the Rich Text Editor does a good job of taking the HTML and enclosing it in the {html} macro.

but it needs to automatically strip the meta tags and other HTML tags outside the body tags, as these tags corrupt the page and don't allow subsequent edits to the page.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-5023].
  {panel}

Deleting large numbers of comments is Really Really Annoying.

Above the comments display, alongside the hide link, add a bulk delete link. Clicking this link redisplays the page, but gives each comment a "delete" checkbox. When the checkbox is ticked, the comment changes colour to show it's been selected.

At the bottom of the page, there's a big delete button that removes all highlighted comments at the same time.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-5002].
  {panel}

A customer has requested the ability to add comments to a specific page via email. 

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of January 30, 2013|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Hi Everyone,
Thanks for your feedback on this issue thus far. We acknowledge that it would be a very useful to be able to add comments to a page via email. We would like to implement it at some point but currently don't have an estimated date for delivering the feature. 

We will update the status of this issue once we have an estimated date for you.

Thank you.  
Bill Arconati,
Product Manager
{panel}

