Since we don't support timezones (see CONF-1026) we should do something to make it easier to understand the times on the Previous Versions page. Either print the current time of the server at the top (so that the user can do the mental conversion) or show the time as relative (9 hours ago).

The same issue would exist on the attachments page as well, if we showed dates with minute precision (which we currently don't -- not sure why not).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4841].
  {panel}

It would be helpful if users could attach updated files with an existing filename.  For example, I like to name my own file revisions like filename_yyyymmdd.ext, and if I uploaded each revision, it would create a new file listing instead of tracking revisions to the same file.  I'd like to be able to attach files with different names to the same file revision tree.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4836].
  {panel}

I would like an option on export space to save only the last version of all documents and attachments.  I would expect the restore operation to restore all the pages and attachments as version 1.  This would be very helpful for populating a secondary site with a clean copy of data.  For instance, I might need to remove confidential data before exporting or there may be preliminary data that I don't want users to see in the history.  It also make the exported zip file smaller especially when large attachments are involved.  I know there are some SQL based work arounds that can help clean up a space after the fact.  These are difficult and error prone.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4823].
  {panel}

Currently confluence will automatically upgrade the database (and possibly other components) without checking the basics have been performed - although an admin *should* RTFM and check the release notes between each upgrade it doesn't hurt to remind them.

It would be great if confluence (upon detecting the version has changed, before changing anything) displays the upgrade path between the old and new versions. Reminding them that they might need to upgrade their database driver, or change a confluence-init.properties variable etc. Even just asking them to confirm that they have taken appropriate backups.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4811].
  {panel}

I'd like to reconfigure the {code} macro to *not* do any syntax highlighting unless a language is specified. Is this possible? Somehow we ended up having lots of pages with Java-syntax-highlighted shell scripts...

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4806].
  {panel}

Currently if you click on any of the sorting options on the attachments page, you can only sort in one direction (e.g. for "name", a-z). This needs to be amended so that if you click again, it reverses the sort order. it would also be nice to have a "direction" arrow here as well (see columns in the MacOS X Finder for an example!)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-4800].
